cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with active learning for anomaly detection, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a novel approach to active learning using ensembles of anomaly detectors. The paper also deals with computer security and fraud prevention, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as another likely category. The use of uncertainty sampling and data drift detection algorithms suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as additional categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of compact descriptions to improve the diversity of instances presented to the analyst, which suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible category.
